/** @page PAGE_CategoryOverview Category and SubCategory Overview

@tableofcontents

@b Categories are used to organize elements for reporting or filtering purposes. 
Each element is in one and only one category.
There is one set of categories per %DgnDb file.
Categories do not nest, but a Category can have SubCategories.

@see DgnCategories
@see DgnCategories::Category
@see DgnCategories::Rank
@see DgnCategories::Scope
@see DgnCategories::Iterator
@see DgnCategoryId

@b SubCategories are used to further organize and subdivide an element's geometry.  
Each piece of geometry is in one and only one SubCategory.
For display purposes, the symbology/appearance for and visibility of the geometry is determined by its SubCategory.
Every Category has a default (unnamed) SubCategory associated with it.

@see DgnCategories::SubCategory
@see DgnCategories::SubCategory::Appearance
@see DgnCategories::SubCategoryIterator
@see DgnSubCategoryId

