@section PAGE_CategoryOverview_SECTION_Category_DgnV8Level Category vs. DgnV8 Level

The concept of a DgnDb @b Category supercedes the concept of a DgnV8 @b Level.
While both have the same primary role (filtering) there are some important differences:

@li For DgnDb, category is equally important to all elements whether they have geometry or not.
@li A DgnDb element is in one and only one category. In DgnV8, a complex element could be on multiple levels.
@li There is one set of categories per DgnDb file. Each model could have its own set of levels in DgnV8.

